Hungary FX Mortgage Plan Is ‘Worrying Precedent,’ Moody’s Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-27T15:38:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/hungary-fx-mortgage-plan-is-worrying-precedent-moody-s-says.html
Hungary’s offer for early repayment
of foreign currency mortgages at below market rates with lenders
swallowing exchange rate losses sets a “worrying precedent,”
Moody’s Investors Service said today.  The plan is “credit negative” for covered bonds, Moody’s
said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  